    <div class="section-divider" style="margin: 0 0 40px;"></div>

    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.04em;">Meeting agenda best practices</h2>
      <div class="insight-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
        <div class="insight-card">
          <div style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">&#9200;</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px;">Time-box everything</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.6;">Assign a duration to every agenda item. Without time limits, discussions expand to fill whatever time is available. A 5-minute item gets 5 minutes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="insight-card">
          <div style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">&#128232;</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px;">Share 24 hours early</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.6;">Send the agenda at least a day before the meeting. This gives attendees time to prepare, read pre-materials, and come ready to contribute.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="insight-card">
          <div style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">&#9989;</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px;">End with action items</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.6;">Every meeting should end with clear next steps: who does what, by when. If a meeting doesn't produce action items, it could have been an email.</p>
        </div>
