    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 48px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px; letter-spacing: -0.04em;">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 15px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); margin-bottom: 24px;">Everything about building effective meeting agendas.</p>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What should a meeting agenda include?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A good agenda includes the meeting title, date and time, attendees, a clear objective, discussion topics with time allocations, and a section for action items or next steps.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How do I share the agenda with my team?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Copy as Text to paste into an email, Slack, or a Google Calendar event description. Copy as Markdown to paste into Google Docs, Notion, or Confluence with formatting preserved.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I set time limits for each item?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Each agenda section has an optional minutes field. The builder automatically calculates your total meeting duration and displays it at the top of the items list.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What makes a meeting agenda effective?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Effective agendas are specific (concrete topics, not vague themes), time-boxed (each item has a duration), shared in advance (at least 24 hours before), and end with clear action items assigned to specific people.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I use this for recurring meetings?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Use the presets as starting templates for standups, project reviews, or 1:1s, then customize each time. Copy and paste the agenda into your recurring calendar event before each meeting.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(31,41,55,0.6), rgba(17,24,39,0.6)); border: 1px solid rgba(75,85,99,0.5); border-radius: 24px; padding: 48px; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.04em;">Automate your meeting prep</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto 24px; line-height: 1.6;">This tool builds one agenda. <a href="/voiceai" style="color: #10b981; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;">Naurra</a> creates agendas, sends them to attendees, and sets up your calendar with a single voice command.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/" style="padding: 14px 28px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #059669); color: white; border-radius: 12px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(16,185,129,0.3);">Try Naurra Free</a>
        <a href="/tools" style="padding: 14px 28px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); border-radius: 12px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;">More free tools</a>
